0) Prereqs

Docker Desktop (Linux) running

Compose v2 (docker compose version)

A valid .env in the project root:

JIRA_DOMAIN=yourcompany.atlassian.net
JIRA_EMAIL=you@company.com
JIRA_TOKEN=xxxxx   # Jira API token


If .env is wrong, the build will succeed but the job will fail at runtime with Jira auth/host errors. Don’t overthink it—fix the secrets.

1) Project Layout (expected)
Report_generator/
├─ Dockerfile
├─ docker-compose.yml
├─ docker.sh
├─ report_script.py
├─ utils/
│   └─ Charts.py
├─ requirements.txt
├─ .env
└─ Reports/           # created automatically; mounted to /app/Reports

2) One-liners (what you actually need)
# Build the image (fresh)
bash docker.sh build

# Bring up a persistent container and stream logs
bash docker.sh up

# Generate the PDF (runs inside the running container)
bash docker.sh generate

# Stop and remove the service
bash docker.sh stop


Deliverable lands here after generate:

./Reports/jira_report.pdf
